obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1721  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig 1 BAI1 is expressed in neurons and localizes to excitatory synapses.\n1b Literal \"We posited that BAI1 might be synaptogenic because of its presence in dendritic spines, apparent even in a low-magnification image\nof a mature hippocampal neuron\"\n1d Literal \"Comparing the gradient of BAI1 staining from spine heads to immediately adjacent segments of dendritic shaft revealed that BAI1 was enriched in spine heads to an extent similar to PSD95, whereas acetylated tubulin was enriched in dendritic shafts and EGFP filled both regions equally.\n1e Literal \"Strikingly, even overexpressed BAI1 targeted strongly to spines\n1f Literal \"First, we biochemically purified synapses and found that BAI1 was enriched in the PSD fraction, although to a lower extent than PSD95\n1g Literal \"Second, we stained mature cultured\nneurons for BAI1 and the synaptic markers PSD95 or GluR1 (Fig.\n1G). In both cases, BAI1 colocalized significantly with these markers in spines, indicative of synaptic localization.\"\n\n9/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.\n- Postsynaptic localization is directly shown in the paper. Term 'integral component of postsynaptic membrane (GO:0099055)' was inferred from TM domains and known rol in cell adhesion.. Experimental description: Experiments were done in rats hippocampus neurons\nLiteral \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from E19 Long-Evans rats as described\npreviously.\"\n\n9/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed BAI1 protein is of human species; \"Human BAI1 was obtained from Y. Nakamura (University of Tokyo) \". Since endogenous rat protein was also visualized annotation is made against rat species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1721" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

